Currency standards were very important even to pre-industrial and ancient societies. A system of weights and measurements would help to foster trade. @L@L
Tampering with currency by counterfeiting or clipping and damaging it would often be considered a major offense and a crime. @L@L
Clipping is shaving or shearing off edges of coins to accumulate extra silver or gold to sell. @L@L
